WEBVTT

00:02:59.447 --> 00:03:01.638
with the coffee table book
about coffee tables,

00:03:01.662 --> 00:03:03.303
where you strike out on your own

00:03:03.327 --> 00:03:06.006
to write a book about people
who strike out on their own.

00:03:06.030 --> 00:03:08.894
DP: What I found was
not so much an economic story,

00:03:08.918 --> 00:03:10.538
but really a psychology story.

00:03:10.562 --> 00:03:13.135
And people were seeking something in work.

00:03:13.159 --> 00:03:15.170
They were seeking a sense of autonomy;

00:03:15.194 --> 00:03:17.778
they were seeking a sense of authenticity;

00:03:17.802 --> 00:03:22.201
they were seeking to do
their own thing their own way.

00:03:22.225 --> 00:03:24.240
AG: You sound like my four-year-old son,

00:03:24.264 --> 00:03:26.604
who said to me the other day,
out of the blue,

00:03:26.628 --> 00:03:28.280
"I can do what I want."

00:03:28.304 --> 00:03:31.646
DP: I actually think that your son
is expressing human nature,